# Project Rules

- **Shadcn UI Styling**: Do not add extra styles or custom classes to shadcn components. 
  - Use only layout-related classes like `flex`, `grid`, `gap`, `justify-*`, `items-*`, etc., when necessary for positioning.
  - Avoid modifying the base styling of the components unless explicitly required.

- **Latest Documentation**: Always refer to the latest documentation before writing code.
  - Use the **Context7 MCP** to stay updated with the latest changes in Next.js and other libraries.
  - Ensure the code follows the most recent best practices and API updates.

- **Code Organization**: Keep the codebase clean and organized.
  - Store `types` and `schemas` in their respective dedicated folders.
  - Create separate files for each major type or schema to maintain modularity.

- **Custom Components**: Follow the established pattern of using custom components (e.g., `PageLayout`, `PageHeader`, `CustomBreadcrumb`) throughout the application.
  - Maintain consistency with existing component usage and structure.

- **Color Usage**: Never use custom hex, RGB, or arbitrary color values (e.g., `bg-[#25D366]`).
  - Always use standard Tailwind color classes or CSS variables defined in [globals.css](file:///d:/Nurulla%20Hasan/elevator_website/src/app/globals.css) (e.g., `text-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `border-border`).
  - Ensure the design stays consistent with the project's theme.
